  "prompt": "What could cause your period to be 14 days late other than pregnancy?",
  "response": "Several factors can cause a delayed period besides pregnancy:\n\n1. Stress\n- High levels of stress can disrupt hormone levels\n- Physical or emotional stress can affect menstrual cycle\n\n2. Hormonal imbalances\n- Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS)\n- Thyroid disorders\n- Hormonal contraceptives\n- Perimenopause\n\n3. Weight changes\n- Significant weight loss\n- Significant weight gain\n- Eating disorders\n\n4. Intense exercise\n- Excessive physical training\n- Extreme athletic activities\n\n5. Medical conditions\n- Diabetes\n- Celiac disease\n- Pituitary tumors\n- Premature ovarian failure\n\n6. Medications\n- Certain antidepressants\n- Some birth control methods\n- Chemotherapy drugs\n\n7. Nutritional deficiencies\n- Low body fat\n- Vitamin D deficiency\n- Iron deficiency\n\n8. Travel or significant lifestyle changes\n- Jet lag\n- Shift work\n- Changes in sleep patterns\n\nWhile these factors can cause a delayed period, it's recommended to take a pregnancy test and consult a healthcare professional if your period is significantly late or irregular.",
